body.name: Rolanstar Bookshelf with Drawer, 7 Shelf Tree Bookshelf, Wooden Bookshelves Storage Rack for CDs/Movies/Books, Rustic Brown Bookcase, Utility Organizer Shelves for Living Room, Bedroom
features: Perfectly Fits Your Room: The rustic tree shaped shelves for an old-time classic, with an attractive vintage appearance and functional design. Beautiful shelves that is perfect for displaying your books, magazines, decorations and novels etc

Space Saving & Large Capacity: Tree Bookshelf dimensions: 7.1"D x 7.1"W x 43.3"H, this bookshelf is very compact and comes with 7 open shelves and 1 bottom drawer. Each shelf can load up to 5-10 books and great for store books, magazines...You can place all your treasures on it

Reliable Raw & Sturdy Design: The Rolanstar tree bookshelf is designed by raw materials, which meets the EPA TSCA Title VI and Carb Certification and a non-woven Drawer, not only provides great stability and durability, but also offers you a safe, healthy and large storage space in your room. It is perfect for accessorizing, organizing, and storing your items while keeping them tidy and organized at living room

15 Minutes Assemble & Easy Cleaning: Comes with included clear and detailed instructions, numbered parts, and a L shaped allen wrench for assembly. And the shelves can easily be cleaned with a wet rag

Wide Application Range: This wooden bookshelf is suitable for any room that needs a bookcase or display shelf and is a perfect furniture piece, featuring elegance, simplicity and practicality, ideal for living room, office, studio, study room, lounge, bookstore etc

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Has a weight limit
reviews.reviewText: Great book stand, don’t fill each tree to the brim with books. It will start to slang forward and looks like it might fall. I have 3-5 books on each and it’s solid. Looks great highly recommend. Set up is pretty easy too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect tabletop bookshelf
reviews.reviewText: Here’s the thing… I have no self control when it comes to books. And, because I have none, when I walk out of the library it’s usually with a tote jam packed with hardcovers (never mind the 30+ purchased books waiting for me at home).Library books though I keep on the small desk in my room and it wasn’t long before I had a small replica of the leaning tower of Pisa. A quick search on Amazon and, et voila, problem solved.This is a sturdy little thing and the perfect size if you want to place it on a desk.The one con would be that apparently it was not the easiest to put together, but I handed that task off so I can’t confirm nor deny 🤷🏻‍♀️🙃

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a great bookshelf. I love the look of it and fits nicely beside my other coffin bookshelf. My only con is that it is not sturdy. It wobbles at the slightest movement. The back is 2 parts and is connected with a thin metal plate, which isn't sturdy either. I have a feeling I will have to replace the metal plates in the back eventually.Also, the stickers are an absolute PAIN to get off. Had to use acetone.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Took a while to put together
reviews.reviewText: My daughter used a drill to screw the parts together.. took her a while but once finished it’s really nice, big and sturdy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Wife loves it!
reviews.reviewText: Purchased as a Christmas gift for my wife, a book lover! The book shelf looks great in design and finish! The assembly was a little confusing for someone that doesn't assemble furniture often. Recommend attaching the shelf to a wall if you have kids or pets that may knock it over.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I love this bookcase. It is the perfect size for my living room. Just a heads up it definitely needs to be anchored as once you put books on it it’ll start leaning forward. But besides that I feel like it’s definitely worth the money and nice quality! Also, it’s easy to put together, my 11 year old did it by Herself.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars High quality wood
reviews.reviewText: Very impressed with this shelf! Very very nice quality wood with a nice grain, packaged safe, and very easy instructions to follow. I would like to add that I would use a Allen wrench bit for your screw driver because this shelf used a lot of Allen wrench screws and it can be hard on your fingers after the 10 screw but other then that it was great! It will be a great addition to my room

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Its decent at first but the weight from the books over time will bend it
reviews.reviewText: Due to the Wood being a Compressed particle board and not actually sturdy wood the weight of the books will make it bend and curve to the point where it will fall over or easily fall over if its not anchored down. I have 4 of these and only one has had this happen and the others are also the same for bending but not as bad. I checked if anything was loose but it is not. I do enjoy these and are a cute design and are sturdy so there is no doubt about that. But just be weary about this for long term use.

This arrived the same day I ordered it. It was packed up with care - nice and tight, with foam between the pieces - and nothing was damaged. The instructions are easy to follow. There are a lot of screws, and you might think you need a third hand to assemble, but I did it by myself, with arthritis in both hands, so I think anyone can do it. Everything lines up as it should. Screws, holes, everything. I really love that, since you are always taking a gamble when you buy something unassembled. lol I really like the look of it. It looks a lot nicer than the photo shows. It also has the cute little drawer in the bottom that is actually quite large. This part you do not have to assemble, it is made of thick canvas and comes folded initially, fitting perfectly in the bottom once assembled. Highly recommend!
